      <section eId="sec_CCRP-779">
        <num>CCRP 779</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-779__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A defendant charged with a misdemeanor in which the punishment, as set forth in the statute defining the offense, may be a fine in excess of one thousand dollars or imprisonment for more than six months shall be tried by a jury of six jurors, all of whom must concur to render a verdict.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-779__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The defendant charged with any other misdemeanor shall be tried by the court without a jury.
Amended by</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112776</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
